                            <comment id="303956" author="scadmin" created="Wed, 9 Jun 2021 09:48:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hiya,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think 2.12 client + RHEL 8.4 also requires &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13182&quot; title=&quot;MAP_POPULATE hangs with Linux 5.4&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13182&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13182&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. that ticket perfectly describes the issue I&apos;m seeing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I grabbed &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/40221/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/40221/&lt;/a&gt; which applies cleanly to 2.12.6 and tested it, and it&apos;s fixed the problem for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;without the MAP_POPULATE patch, nodes with root-on-lustre don&apos;t reboot and logrotate hangs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;RHEL/centos 8.3 didn&apos;t need this patch, so I guess it&apos;s an 8.4 kernel change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
robin&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
